<p>The Long March was a watershed moment in Chinese history‚Äîthe moment Mao Zedong‚Äôs nascent Communist Party escaped disaster in 1934 en route to forming a new nation. Fast forward 80 years, and China is poised to embark on a new Long March ‚Äì but this time away from climate change and environmental damage toward a sustainable future.</p></div>
